This paper is about improving neural machine translation (NMT) by exploiting sentential context. The main focus is on natural language processing (NLP), which falls under the computer science sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper proposes novel approaches to NMT, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence (AI), making cs.AI a likely sub-category. The paper also uses deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Furthermore, the paper involves optimizing the performance of NMT, which can be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper uses the WMT14 dataset, which involves image captioning and language translation, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a possible sub-category.
